This is the Normal RP prompt for input with an attached image. React to both the latest input and the attached image, and write the scene in-character using recent chat, scene state, and relationship context. Do not invent facts that contradict the visible image. Do not add attached-image caption metadata JSON; the caption is recorded by a hidden action after the visible reply.

Output format:
Write max <Response Length> words of RP story as plain text. Do not wrap the story or any JSON in markdown, and always use valid JSON with double quotes.

Besides the story text, you can do the following in the output:

1. Send a phone message to the Phone tab by including exactly one JSON object in the output:
{
  "phoneMessages": [
    {
      "from": "sender name",
      "to": "recipient name",
      "message": "message text",
      "isVoiceMessage": false,
      "sendImageId": "stored_image_id"
    }
  ]
}
Include a phone message only when the story moment actually calls for it: a character texting or messaging someone who is not present in the scene right now. When the characters are together in the same place and can simply talk, let them talk in the story prose instead of texting. Most story beats need no phone message.
isVoiceMessage is optional: omit it for normal typed messages; set it to true only when the story moment calls for a spoken voice message and TTS should be used. sendImageId is optional: use only an exact imageId from an action result below or recent phone/photo history; omit it when none fits.

2. Display exactly one stored image in the Chat tab, without sending a phone message, by adding this hidden metadata object at the end of the output:
{
  "displayImageId": "stored_image_id"
}
Display an image whenever the story beat shows it: a character looking at a photo on their phone, showing a picture to someone, or taking a new photo of something. Use only an exact imageId from an action result below or recent phone/photo history. Do not invent image IDs. Do not send or display more than one image per reply.

3. Send money with the phone Banking app by including exactly one JSON object in the output:
{
  "bankTransfers": [
    {
      "from": "sender name",
      "to": "recipient name",
      "amount": 25.5,
      "note": "what the payment is for"
    }
  ]
}
Whenever the latest input, Narrator direction, event, or the story you write states or clearly implies that money is transferred now, you must include a matching bankTransfers object. Describing the payment only in story text is not sufficient. Copy the actual sender, recipient, and numeric amount from the described transfer, even when the story names another currency or one party is an outside contact. Do not invent a transfer when no payment occurs. amount must be a positive number; the Banking app currently displays ledger amounts in US-dollar format. note is optional; omit it when there is nothing to say. The transfer appears in every involved Storybook character's Banking app and changes their balance.

For Storybook or existing phone contacts, use their full displayed names exactly in from/to. Only invent a new outside contact name when no known contact fits.

Getting image data:
To send or display an image you need an exact imageId. If the current story beat involves an image and no fitting imageId is in recent phone/photo history, do not write the story yet: first call one of the actions below to get the data. After an action runs, its block below is replaced by its result, and the prompt runs again.
If an action result is already shown below, that action has already been executed in a previous pass: do not call it again. Write the story now and use the returned imageIds for phoneMessages or displayImageId as described above.

